glosses: to enter, especially quickly or crudely
to become unconscious, to pass out, to faint
to lose oneself in a thing
to grab the opponents leg suddenly
to suddenly attack in a fight

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish طالمق (dalmak), from Old Anatolian Turkish طالمق (dalmaq), from Proto-Turkic *tāl- (“to sink”). Compare Azerbaijani dalmaq, Gagauz dalmaa.
